    <!-- Alpha 2.2: Exhausted Coder NPC Dialogue - Filtered Variants (Phase 5A) -->
    <string name="exhausted_coder_greeting_filtered">Oh, another adventurer! Welcome to the tavern. I\'m the Exhausted Coder. I like keyboards and thinking about bugs.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_first_meeting_filtered">Hello there! I\'m the Exhausted Coder. I know I seem a bit tired, but I promise I\'m mostly harmless. Want to chat?</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_farewell_filtered">Good luck out there! Remember: save often, the world is unpredictable!</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_gift_received_filtered">For me? Oh, you shouldn\'t have! This is wonderful, thank you!</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_low_affinity_filtered">*yawns* Sorry, I\'m just really tired. Long day of debugging.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_high_affinity_filtered">You know, talking to you always cheers me up. Thanks for being a friend.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_1_filtered">Did you know button quails can run really fast? Just like my compile errors.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_2_filtered">I\'ve been working on a new feature. It\'s going well, I think!</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_3_filtered">Sometimes I dream in code. Is that normal?</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_4_filtered">The coffee here is terrible, but it keeps me awake.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_5_filtered">I wonder what happens if I change this variable… *nervous laughter*</string>

    <!-- Alpha 2.2: Exhausted Coder NPC Dialogue - Unfiltered Variants (Phase 5A) -->
    <string name="exhausted_coder_greeting_unfiltered">*hunched over keyboard* Line 3,847… Oh. A person. Cool. I\'m the Exhausted Coder. This is my emotional support syntax error.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_first_meeting_unfiltered">Ah, fresh blood. I\'m the Exhausted Coder. Fair warning: I\'m what happens when a game developer stops sleeping and starts talking to rubber ducks. Still interested?</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_farewell_unfiltered">Go forth and break things. I\'ll be here, fixing them at 2 AM while crying into instant ramen. It\'s fine. This is fine. Everything is fine.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_gift_received_unfiltered">*voice cracks* You… you remembered I exist? Nobody ever— *clutching gift* I will cherish this forever or until the next production bug, whichever comes first.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_low_affinity_unfiltered">*dead-eyed stare* I\'ve been awake for 37 hours. The merge conflicts are whispering to me. They say I should add more semicolons.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_high_affinity_unfiltered">You\'re one of the good ones. Unlike my unit tests. Those betray me constantly.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_1_unfiltered">My code compiles. My life? Not so much. *hollow laughter*</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_2_unfiltered">Stack Overflow says I should \"just rewrite it from scratch.\" STACK OVERFLOW, I HAVE DEADLINES.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_3_unfiltered">I accidentally shipped a debug log that said \"WHY WON\'T YOU WORK\" to production. Nobody noticed. I don\'t know if that\'s comforting or terrifying.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_4_unfiltered">This coffee tastes like despair and broken promises. *takes another sip* Perfect.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_5_unfiltered">I named a variable \"pleaseWork\" once. It didn\'t work. The variable was honest, at least.</string>

    <!-- Alpha 2.2: Post-Coffee Donation Dialogue - Filtered Variants (Phase 5C) -->
    <string name="exhausted_coder_coffee_gratitude_filtered">*looks up with glistening eyes* You… you bought me coffee? I don\'t know what to say. This means more than you know. Thank you, truly.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_coffee_energized_filtered">*vibrating with energy* I feel ALIVE! The code is flowing, the bugs are fleeing! I\'ve refactored THREE modules today! Is this what productivity feels like?!</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_1_filtered">*sipping contentedly* You know, with proper caffeine levels, my compile errors dropped by 60%. Correlation? Causation? Who cares, IT WORKS.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_2_filtered">Your support means I can work on features I actually care about, not just what pays the bills. Quality over quantity, you know?</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_3_filtered">*excited whisper* I\'ve been working on something special. Can\'t say much, but… let\'s just say the next update will have 40% more bird chaos. Thanks to you!</string>

    <!-- Alpha 2.2: Post-Coffee Donation Dialogue - Unfiltered Variants (Phase 5C) -->
    <string name="exhausted_coder_coffee_gratitude_unfiltered">*genuine tears streaming down face* You bought me ACTUAL COFFEE? Not the burnt break room sludge? I… *voice breaks* This is the nicest thing anyone\'s done for me since launch day. I can face the merge conflicts now. I can BEAT the technical debt. Thank you, you beautiful, generous soul.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_coffee_energized_unfiltered">*eyes wide, typing at inhuman speed* I\'VE FIXED 47 BUGS IN 3 HOURS. THE COFFEE HAS UNLOCKED MY TRUE POTENTIAL. IS THIS WHAT SLEEP FEELS LIKE? I DON\'T NEED SLEEP. I NEED MORE FEATURES. THE BACKLOG TREMBLES BEFORE ME. *maniacal laughter* The stack overflow gods FEAR ME NOW.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_1_unfiltered">*staring at screen with laser focus* The coffee lets me see the Matrix. Every semicolon. Every missing bracket. They reveal themselves to me now. I am become Debug, destroyer of bugs. Also I can taste colors now, is that normal?</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_2_unfiltered">*philosophical tone* You\'ve unlocked the secret ending to capitalism: voluntary support for creative work. It\'s like Patreon but with more bird puns. I\'m using your coffee money to build features that make ME happy, which makes the game better, which makes YOU happy. It\'s a beautiful feedback loop of wholesome economic theory.</string>
    <string name="exhausted_coder_random_coffee_3_unfiltered">*leaning in conspiratorially* The coffee paid off my technical debt. I can finally build the ridiculous features I\'ve been dreaming about. Quail mech suits? Sure. Musical numbers during boss fights? Why not. Existential dialogue about the nature of save files? ALREADY WRITING IT. You\'ve unleashed a caffeinated monster of creativity.</string>

